commitResults.messageBody:
Assertions can assist in the identification of bugs at a specific location efficiently

Identifying critical points in the code and adding assertions in these areas

This allows us to target areas in the code that are most vulnerable and allow
for fast rectification whenever a problem occurs

Refer to the JavaPoint tutorial about assertions
https://www.javatpoint.com/assertion-in-java

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code to adhere to the Code Quality guidelines
commitResults.messageBody:
To increase the understandability of the code.

Changing portions of code that contain long methods, deep nesting, complicated expressions and magic literals.

This allows the user to better understand and follow the purpose of the code written.

Information about code quality can be found here
https://nus-cs2103-ay2122s2.github.io/website/se-book-adapted/chapters/codeQuality.html#code-quality
